    <section>
        <title>Cost and time overruns</title>
        <para> The Standish group report found that in 1994 the average cost across all projects was
            178% of the original cost estimate. This was reduced to 169% in the 1998 study, 145% in
            the 2000 study </para>
        <para> In 1994 the average time overrun across all 8380 projects was found to be 222% of the
            original time estimate. At the time of the report there were 3682 active projects across
            365 organizations. Of these on 431 or 12% were at the time of the publication of the
            report on-time and on-budget. </para>
        <para> This figure was reduced to 63% of all projects in 2000. </para>
        <para> In 2003, 51% of projects experienced cost or time overruns or delivered incomplete or
            incorrect functionality. </para>

    </section>

    <section>
        <title>Content deficiencies</title>
        <para> The 1994 study found that on average, projects were delivered with only 61% of
            features originally specified. </para>
